    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Aphelagathis verticalis A – D = neotype ♀, E – F = melanic specimen. A. lateral habitus, arrow indicates slightly thickened area of ovipositor. B. dorsal habitus, arrows indicate propodeum and first median tergite. C. wings, arrow indicates pigmented Cub vein of hind wing. D. lateral head and mesosoma. E. lateral head and mesosoma. F. dorsal head, mesosoma ant first median tergite." ;
